fields.title: Ballet Dancers in Red - Ballet Painting
fields.description: Ballet is created on beautiful lines and shapes. If what you hear and what you see mesh, there's a very thrilling experience.

fields.title: Ripping up the Ice - Ice Skating Painting
fields.description: Dancing on ice has always been a favourite to watch with professional skaters swirling, spinning and jumping in a blur of colour making you wish you where that agile again. With the Winter Olympics this is all making it exciting again.

fields.title: Tour de France Femmes Touched - Cycling Painting
fields.description: When you put out a hand to connect with the fans. Marianne Vos (Jumbo-Visma) won stage six of the race, from Saint-Die-Des-Vosges to Rosheim

fields.title: Trusting Him - Trapeze Painting
fields.description: This is loosely based on an image of trapeze artists. I feel the speed of the swing going through the air and the trust needed to perform these acts. You under the spotlight in the big top and you can afford to make a mistake. Its all smoke and mirrors in the depiction of the background.

fields.title: Whitby Harbour - Seascape Painting
fields.description: Looking over the harbour from the cliffs. A fleeting impression

fields.title: London Blue River - Cityscape Painting
fields.description: A view of London along the Thames showing Tour bridge, Town hall and Shard. On a clear day this an iconic view catching the reflections of an ever changing city.

fields.title: Beach walkers - Seascape
fields.description: I love walking on beaches when the weather is not at its prime. Put on a big coat and enjoy the wind, big skies and prancing waves. Filey beach

fields.title: Flower Girls - Cow Painting
fields.description: Friends are often the inspiration for my paintings. A good friend sent me an image from her travels as she knows I love painting cows. I really loved the movement in the legs and the quirky nature of the subject matter. I can just see the big old mother being stern and grumpy while the younger ones in orange and pick are far more frivolous.

fields.title: Mother and calf
fields.description: Pen and ink drawing of a cow with her calf. I have kept the palette monotone with sepia and black inks. This is something a come across often when out walking and beware a mother protecting her off spring .

fields.title: I walked London until the cows came home - Cow Painting
fields.description: When I go to London I tend to walk for miles. I love just absorbing the cities energy. After reading 'Jeff in Venice, Death in Varanasi' by Geoff Dyer I thought of painting cows in the middle of London. Can you imagine the chaos of cattle on the streets?

fields.title: Sip
fields.description: An abstracted human figure sips from their hand; the figure is shaded with a blend of dark and light oranges giving them a corroded metal appearance.
